wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:1024px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:56.25%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/b95e4/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 256w,\n/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/1779b/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 512w,\n/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/87945/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 1024w,\n/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/5a523/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcSet=\"/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/b95e4/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 256w,\n/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/1779b/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 512w,\n/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/87945/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 1024w,\n/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/5a523/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 1200w\" src=\"/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/87945/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg\" alt=\"An image of Live Poker&#x27;s latest magazine cover featuring Tony Parker against a black backdrop\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/b95e4/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 256w,\n/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/1779b/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 512w,\n/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/87945/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 1024w,\n/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/5a523/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcset=\"/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/b95e4/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 256w,\n/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/1779b/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 512w,\n/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/87945/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 1024w,\n/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/5a523/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg 1200w\" src=\"/static/33608a9f605f14f1f65e126855aad541/87945/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg\" alt=\"An image of Live Poker's latest magazine cover featuring Tony Parker against a black backdrop\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>After a one-year hiatus due to the COVID pandemic, the <a href=\"https://www.wsop.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>World Series of Poker</strong></a> returns to its traditional home at the <a href=\"https://www.googleadservices.com/pagead/aclk?sa=L&amp;ai=DChcSEwjc6q-M5cTwAhXu5uMHHVo2Av4YABAAGgJ5bQ&amp;ohost=www.google.com&amp;cid=CAESQOD2Vi8y9d9htibPG0J__p4cGrquWtBb0cDKdYRjuUhHb-OUayYXPmNzX20v--CB5Wgjio3-yYiFZcZHug_mFkA&amp;sig=AOD64_2wdWJVmR3eqBsQwHJ3QmpMX2x-eA&amp;q&amp;adurl&amp;ved=2ahUKEwi6xKSM5cTwAhXJZs0KHe_LBOcQ0Qx6BAgFEAE\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Rio All-Suite Hotel &amp; Casino</strong></a> in Las Vegas starting September 30<sup>th</sup>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This marathon of poker events runs for seven weeks with the coveted ‘<a href=\"https://www.wsop.com/news/2021/Apr/12416/WORLD-SERIES-OF-POKER-ANNOUNCES-PLANS-FOR-2021.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>WSOP Main Event</strong></a>’ scheduled to kick-off on Thursday November 4<sup>th</sup> and runs through Wednesday November 17<sup>th</sup>. The Main Event champion typically wins 5-7 million dollars and this year a new challenger has emerged.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The former <a href=\"https://www.nba.com/spurs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>San Antonio Spurs</strong></a> basketball star and future NBA Hall of Famer, Tony Parker, will be playing at the WSOP Main Event for the very first time. It would be a miscalculated mistake to count Tony out.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Just this past January 16<sup>th</sup>, Tony defeated over 200 <a href=\"https://texasholdemsa.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Texas Hold ‘Em Charity Poker</strong></a> players to win our charity poker tournament and take the $25,000 grand prize. That win, catapulted Tony to worldwide poker fame and he was invited to play in the WSOP Main Event. The charity fundraiser also raised a hefty $70,000 for <a href=\"https://sanantoniosports.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>San Antonio Sports</strong></a>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Recently, the French edition of <em><a href=\"https://www.livepoker.fr/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Live</strong><strong>Poker</strong></a></em> featured Tony Parker on its May 2021 magazine cover and anointed him as a sensational ‘Poker All-Star!’</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Without a doubt, the entire City of San Antonio will be rooting for Tony to win it all at the WSOP…..and it all started here with <a href=\"https://thepmgrp.com/agency-news/tony-parker-scores-another-championship/\">our charity poker event!</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Good luck TP!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://thepmgrp.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">About The PM Group</a>:</strong> The PM Group was founded in 1988. For over 33 years, the agency has continued to grow and is San Antonio’s largest marketing and advertising agency. The PM Group’s client roster spans numerous industries including home services, automotive, CPG, entertainment and sports marketing, legal, business services, non-profits, real estate and fitness. For two consecutive years now, the Agency has set annual revenue records with the addition of six new clients and through the continued success of our existing clients. Additionally, the agency hosts their annual Charity Gala that to date has raised millions of dollars for local San Antonio area non-profit organizations in the last 15 years! In 2020 alone, the Agency donated over $1,050,000 to local non-profits. It is our way of giving back to the community that we so humbly serve.</p>\n","title":"First Tony Parker Wins Our Charity Poker Tournament and Then Becomes a Worldwide Poker All-Star!","seo":{"breadcrumbs":[{"text":"First Tony Parker Wins Our Charity Poker Tournament and Then Becomes a Worldwide Poker All-Star!","url":"/first-tony-parker-wins-our-charity-poker-tournament-and-then-becomes-a-worldwide-poker-all-star/"}],"title":"Tony Parker to Play in World Series of Poker | The PM Group","metaDesc":"Tony Parker won The PM Group’s Texas Hold ‘Em Charity Poker Tournament and went on to become a WSOP All-Star.","focuskw":"Tony Parker","metaKeywords":"","metaRobotsNoindex":"index","metaRobotsNofollow":"follow","opengraphTitle":"Tony Parker to Play in World Series of Poker | The PM Group","opengraphDescription":"Tony Parker won The PM Group’s Texas Hold ‘Em Charity Poker Tournament and went on to become a WSOP All-Star.","opengraphImage":{"altText":"An image of Live Poker's latest magazine cover featuring Tony Parker against a black backdrop","sourceUrl":"https://thepmgroup.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_.jpg","srcSet":"https://thepmgroup.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thepmgroup.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Image-5.14.21-Tony.Parker.Poker_-1024x576.jpg 1024w, ht